<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/42958375-juan-camilo-infante-mindernickel"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1431315706i/42958375.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/42958375-juan-camilo-infante-mindernickel">Juan Camilo Infante (Mindernickel)</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I actually liked it. He does not pretend to be perfect. And I have seen people in a lot of relationships cheating, so I dont see why denying that part<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I actually liked it. He does not pretend to be perfect. And I have seen people in a lot of relationships cheating, so I dont see why denying that part of a lot of peoples lives<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
