        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2717264905" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12218547184361462623"><b>Actual rating:2.5⭐</b><br/><br/>Too many questions unanswered , too much work for my little brain 🙄.I am so confused . Not sure what to feel here .This was the BOTM for our Overbooked Book club. I will say this,it&apos;s definitely a great pick for book clubs - good for discussions because most of the story is left to your own interpretation.<br/><br/><b>First the pros </b>: Started out as a coming-of-age story.I liked the flow, enjoyed the writing , the pacing- no issues here. Although I hated Hajime from the bottom of my heart, </span>
  <span id="freeText12218547184361462623" style="display:none"><b>Actual rating:2.5⭐</b><br /><br />Too many questions unanswered , too much work for my little brain 🙄.I am so confused . Not sure what to feel here .This was the BOTM for our Overbooked Book club. I will say this,it's definitely a great pick for book clubs - good for discussions because most of the story is left to your own interpretation.<br /><br /><b>First the pros </b>: Started out as a coming-of-age story.I liked the flow, enjoyed the writing , the pacing- no issues here. Although I hated Hajime from the bottom of my heart, I still wanted to know what happens to him. <br /><br /><b>What I didn't like :</b><br />I understand that Murakami's intend was to give us a highly flawed protagonist in Hajime. At one point, Hajime himself tells :<br /><br /><b>
  <i>"I'm a selfish, hopeless, worthless human being".</i>
</b><br /><br />This summarizes him exactly. For me , it's difficult to feel anything for such a guy. And anyways most of the problems seemed self created. He seemed hell-bent on ruining everything good in his life for no apparent reason.<br /><br />And the epic love for the mysterious Shimamoto- again I couldn't feel anything. He cares so deeply about this girl about whom he (and we) barely knows anything. I don't understand this <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Yeah, there is this whole idea that may be she wasn't even real(disappearance of money)...who knows , we'll never know I guess) <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>His whole attitude while cheating his girlfriend and his wife was just too casual , in my opinion. I don't get his mindset.May be there is some really deep internal meaning which was frankly too deep for me to grasp 🙏. <br /><br />Overall, I felt an overwhelming sense of sadness while reading -for whom or why I have no clue. The ending was open - ended , I have no clue what to make of that either. It felt as if I just saw a person's life from point A to point B..and Boom! done. We get these random details about someone's life that added up to absolutely nothing <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[What's with the father -in -law? we learn about his illegal trades etc. and then ?? <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>.What's the takeaway?<br /><br /><br /> <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12218547184361462623" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
