<div id="review_2936784466" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2936784466" />
    <a title="Prashasti " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13581884-prashasti"><img alt="Prashasti " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1585201015p2/13581884.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2936784466?book_show_action=true">Aug 21, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Prashasti " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Prashasti " href="/user/show/13581884-prashasti">Prashasti </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/15840207-south-of-the-border-west-of-the-sun">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2936784466" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15828769217526169025"><b>
  <i>“The sad truth is that certain types of things can&apos;t go backward. Once they start going forward, no matter what you do, they can&apos;t go back the way they were. If even one little thing goes awry, then that&apos;s how it will stay forever.”</i>
</b><br/> <br/>A very typical of Murakami to delineate the zest of modern-day Tokyo and to spin a nexus of episodes revolving around it. I thoroughly enjoyed the descriptions of Suburban Japan, that were oft mentioned in the story. <br/>If you&apos;re someone who enjoyed reading Norwegia</span>
  <span id="freeText15828769217526169025" style="display:none"><b>
  <i>“The sad truth is that certain types of things can't go backward. Once they start going forward, no matter what you do, they can't go back the way they were. If even one little thing goes awry, then that's how it will stay forever.”</i>
</b><br /> <br />A very typical of Murakami to delineate the zest of modern-day Tokyo and to spin a nexus of episodes revolving around it. I thoroughly enjoyed the descriptions of Suburban Japan, that were oft mentioned in the story. <br />If you're someone who enjoyed reading Norwegian Woods, which happens to be my first &amp; favorite book by Murakami, you'd certainly able to like this book as well.<br /><br />You know you're totally into reading Murakami books, when you become so used to the cliffhangers that you don't expect any other kind of ending.<br />I didn't feel like finding any answers to that <br />Reason?<br /><br />Hajime. <br />Had it not been Murakami, I probably wouldn't have continued reading anything more about him ( Okay, I'm kinda lying I obviously wanted to know what happened to him and his mystery girl ).<br />But seriously, what a jerk of a character Murakami penned down, he isn't just a highly-flawed character, but also a definition of an utter cracknob . I absolutely hated him for the things that he did, and the fact that he escaped away from all his sins so easily makes me hate him even more. And, at the end I expected him to show a hecking bit of responsibility towards himself and his actions but guess what? He still gets away with this- <i>I may end up being like that again...</i> and guess what? He's taken back with all that ratshit. I feel so sorry for you, Mrs. Doormat!<br /><br />The bizzare air of suspense, oddly flawed characters, jazz music, and an open to interpret ending...you have it all! <br />PS: Feels so good to finally get out of a reading slump!</span>
  <a data-text-id="15828769217526169025" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review2936784466">
  <td colspan="2">
    <div class="updateActionLinks">
        <a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link2936784466" title="Flag this review as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=2936784466&amp;resource_type=Review&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F17799.South_of_the_Border_West_of_the_Sun">flag</a>





      <span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_review_2936784466'><a id="like_count_review_2936784466" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/2936784466?resource_type=Review"><span class="likesCount">22 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it gr-button gr-button--small" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F17799.South_of_the_Border_West_of_the_Sun">Like</a></span>
